1
00:01:04,152 --> 00:01:06,988
QUEEN OF TEARS

2
00:01:20,710 --> 00:01:21,795
Stop.

3
00:01:36,643 --> 00:01:38,353
I recognize that truck.

4
00:01:44,567 --> 00:01:45,735
I did find it odd

5
00:01:45,819 --> 00:01:48,488
when my grandfather suddenly wanted

6
00:01:48,571 --> 00:01:51,407
to change the ventilators
and told us to leave.

7
00:01:51,491 --> 00:01:53,660
That's the day I saw that truck.

8
00:01:53,743 --> 00:01:56,121
So you think that truck
carried his secret fund?

9
00:01:56,204 --> 00:01:59,457
If I'm right,
wouldn't the money be at home?

10
00:02:09,676 --> 00:02:10,552
EPISODE 12

11
00:02:21,688 --> 00:02:22,856
You shouldn't get wet.

12
00:02:22,939 --> 00:02:25,316
Wait here while I bring the car over.

13
00:02:53,887 --> 00:02:55,805
You have arrived at your destination.

14
00:03:19,287 --> 00:03:20,288
Hae-in.

15
00:03:25,293 --> 00:03:26,252
Hyun-woo.

16
00:03:35,595 --> 00:03:36,679
That was quick.

17
00:03:41,935 --> 00:03:43,228
Why are you out here?

18
00:03:43,311 --> 00:03:44,229
Get up.

19
00:03:53,112 --> 00:03:54,113
I was a bit dizzy.

20
00:03:57,116 --> 00:03:58,534
I'm hungry too.

21
00:04:02,247 --> 00:04:04,540
Let's have something tasty
before we go home.

22
00:04:12,423 --> 00:04:13,258
Sure.

23
00:05:43,723 --> 00:05:45,600
-Are you okay?
-Yes.

24
00:05:46,100 --> 00:05:47,352
Should we call the police?

25
00:05:47,435 --> 00:05:48,686
-Wait.
-We should.

26
00:05:48,770 --> 00:05:50,980
You were attacked
by three men last time too.

27
00:06:50,289 --> 00:06:51,124
You're…

28
00:06:53,084 --> 00:06:53,918
Eun-sung.

29
00:06:54,627 --> 00:06:57,088
What? Do you recognize me now?

30
00:06:58,756 --> 00:06:59,590
What a shame.

31
00:07:03,803 --> 00:07:05,138
How could I…

32
00:07:05,221 --> 00:07:07,682
Exactly. How could you mistake me

33
00:07:07,765 --> 00:07:09,100
for Hyun-woo?

34
00:07:12,603 --> 00:07:13,604
Hae-in!

35
00:07:20,736 --> 00:07:21,737
Open the door.

36
00:07:23,948 --> 00:07:24,782
And if I do?

37
00:07:26,075 --> 00:07:27,243
What will you tell him?

38
00:07:28,202 --> 00:07:29,829
-What?
-Are you going to tell him?

39
00:07:29,912 --> 00:07:32,707
That you got in my car
after mistaking me for him?

40
00:07:48,139 --> 00:07:49,515
He'll be shocked.

41
00:07:49,599 --> 00:07:51,851
Wouldn't it be better if you said

42
00:07:52,727 --> 00:07:54,020
we were going somewhere?

43
00:07:56,439 --> 00:07:57,440
Hae-in.

44
00:08:03,863 --> 00:08:05,156
Open the door.

45
00:08:08,743 --> 00:08:09,994
Open it.

46
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:26,177
Are you okay?

47
00:08:27,220 --> 00:08:28,846
Yes, I'm fine.

48
00:08:30,681 --> 00:08:31,807
Then I'm relieved.

49
00:08:37,396 --> 00:08:39,690
I thought something happened to you.

50
00:08:40,566 --> 00:08:41,442
Let's go.

51
00:09:00,545 --> 00:09:02,797
I ran into Eun-sung earlier.

52
00:09:03,422 --> 00:09:05,174
And he invited me back home.

53
00:09:07,218 --> 00:09:09,554
You know I've wanted to see Grandfather.

54
00:09:16,310 --> 00:09:17,645
I'll be back.

55
00:09:19,313 --> 00:09:20,439
I understand.

56
00:09:21,732 --> 00:09:22,692
Let me go with you.

57
00:09:22,775 --> 00:09:24,318
I'm sorry,

58
00:09:24,402 --> 00:09:26,153
but I only invited her.

59
00:09:31,367 --> 00:09:32,201
Don't worry.

60
00:09:34,328 --> 00:09:35,496
Just pick me up later.

61
00:09:36,831 --> 00:09:38,082
Are you sure you're okay?

62
00:09:40,626 --> 00:09:42,461
Yes, I'm fine.

63
00:10:48,486 --> 00:10:49,362
Surprise.

64
00:10:49,445 --> 00:10:50,571
How did you find me?

65
00:10:54,575 --> 00:10:55,910
What's wrong?

66
00:10:56,619 --> 00:11:00,247
-Aren't you glad to see me?
-I mean, I was going to call.

67
00:11:01,207 --> 00:11:02,792
I see.

68
00:11:02,875 --> 00:11:05,711
Jeez, I had no idea.

69
00:11:08,172 --> 00:11:11,175
So I thought of killing you
once I tracked you down.

70
00:11:18,766 --> 00:11:20,101
Geon-u.

71
00:11:21,227 --> 00:11:24,772
Is this him?
Jeez, he looks better in photos.

72
00:11:25,856 --> 00:11:27,316
Hey, Dong-u.

73
00:11:27,400 --> 00:11:29,276
Say, "Daddy."

74
00:11:29,360 --> 00:11:30,903
-His name is Geon-u.
-Hey.

75
00:11:30,986 --> 00:11:33,698
I named my son Dong-u, so that's his name.

76
00:11:33,781 --> 00:11:36,659
Anyway, it must've been tough

77
00:11:36,742 --> 00:11:39,245
to live with a dense idiot.

78
00:11:40,454 --> 00:11:43,207
Soo-cheol will be arrested soon.

79
00:11:43,290 --> 00:11:45,584
-Why?
-I did some illegal deeds

80
00:11:45,668 --> 00:11:46,752
as a finance director.

81
00:11:46,836 --> 00:11:50,005
I planned it out
so that he'd take the blame.

82
00:11:50,089 --> 00:11:53,259
I tipped off a prosecutor
before leaving Korea.

83
00:11:53,342 --> 00:11:55,136
-You didn't have to do that--
-Hey.

84
00:11:55,219 --> 00:11:57,388
I did it all for you.

85
00:11:57,471 --> 00:12:00,516
What if he wants revenge
and comes looking for you?

86
00:12:09,859 --> 00:12:12,695
God, he's noisy. Hey!

87
00:12:13,654 --> 00:12:15,030
Do that in the bathroom.

88
00:12:18,534 --> 00:12:20,745
The person you dialed is unavailable.

89
00:12:20,828 --> 00:12:22,079
MY SON, HYUN-WOO

90
00:12:22,163 --> 00:12:24,457
Hyun-woo and Hae-in aren't picking up.

91
00:12:24,540 --> 00:12:26,500
Are they spending the night in Seoul?

92
00:12:26,584 --> 00:12:28,794
That's better than driving back
at this hour.

93
00:12:29,920 --> 00:12:31,464
Honey, don't you think

94
00:12:31,547 --> 00:12:33,591
-we're being too liberal?
-What do you mean?

95
00:12:33,674 --> 00:12:35,426
Forget about Hae-in.

96
00:12:35,509 --> 00:12:38,262
Hyun-woo didn't even go abroad to study.

97
00:12:38,345 --> 00:12:40,222
Don't you think he's too open-minded?

98
00:12:40,306 --> 00:12:41,223
What's the issue?

99
00:12:41,307 --> 00:12:43,225
They're not strangers.

100
00:12:43,934 --> 00:12:48,481
Divorced couples
are more distant than strangers.

101
00:12:50,858 --> 00:12:53,402
-Is this right?
-This isn't your first rodeo.

102
00:12:54,111 --> 00:12:57,406
What did you say when you heard
Hyun-woo was marrying into that family?

103
00:12:57,490 --> 00:12:58,949
"Is this right?"

104
00:12:59,033 --> 00:13:00,701
And when he decided to divorce?

105
00:13:00,785 --> 00:13:02,036
"Is this right?"

106
00:13:02,119 --> 00:13:05,331
And when he first brought
his in-laws to stay here,

107
00:13:05,414 --> 00:13:07,374
didn't you say the same thing?

108
00:13:07,458 --> 00:13:08,292
I did.

109
00:13:08,375 --> 00:13:10,211
"Is this right? Is this wrong?"

110
00:13:10,294 --> 00:13:13,172
There's no point in worrying.
Life will take its course.

111
00:13:13,255 --> 00:13:15,299
-Let them be.
-You're right.

112
00:13:16,050 --> 00:13:18,302
Honey, have you seen his eyes lately?

113
00:13:19,303 --> 00:13:21,347
There's no turning back for him now.

114
00:13:22,473 --> 00:13:24,600
No one can stop him.

115
00:13:25,643 --> 00:13:27,102
Then stop it already.

116
00:13:27,978 --> 00:13:30,189
-What?
-Stop calling him.

117
00:13:30,272 --> 00:13:31,106
Okay.

118
00:13:49,750 --> 00:13:50,626
MISSED CALLS
FATHER

119
00:13:55,089 --> 00:13:57,007
What? What's going on?

120
00:13:58,676 --> 00:13:59,802
Hey.

121
00:14:00,302 --> 00:14:02,137
-You're up.
-What have you done to me?

122
00:14:02,847 --> 00:14:03,681
What is this?

123
00:14:03,764 --> 00:14:06,183
God, you're noisy. Go back to sleep, okay?

124
00:14:06,267 --> 00:14:10,563
I'll light up a briquette
to keep you warm while you sleep.

125
00:14:27,121 --> 00:14:28,122
Why are we here?

126
00:14:29,164 --> 00:14:32,751
-I want to see my Grandfather.
-You're wet and cold. Get changed first.

127
00:14:33,586 --> 00:14:34,628
And let's eat.

128
00:14:37,047 --> 00:14:38,299
That's not why I'm here.

129
00:14:38,382 --> 00:14:40,050
That's why I brought you here.

130
00:14:42,428 --> 00:14:44,722
Get changed and eat with me.

131
00:14:44,805 --> 00:14:46,265
Then you can see him.

132
00:15:06,619 --> 00:15:09,663
-Is the steak almost ready?
-Yes, sir. I made yuzu salad.

133
00:15:09,747 --> 00:15:11,540
It's her favorite.

134
00:15:11,624 --> 00:15:14,418
Good. I'll pick the wine.

135
00:15:14,501 --> 00:15:15,878
As for the plate…

136
00:15:18,589 --> 00:15:19,548
This one.

137
00:15:19,632 --> 00:15:20,883
-Okay.
-And for the wine…

138
00:15:24,136 --> 00:15:24,970
Use this.

139
00:15:47,242 --> 00:15:48,369
MR. PYEON

140
00:15:50,454 --> 00:15:52,247
-What is it?
-I got rid of Mr. Baek.

141
00:15:55,042 --> 00:15:56,919
-Are you sure?
-Yes. What should I do now?

142
00:15:58,504 --> 00:16:00,339
Don't call me and lie low for now.

143
00:16:00,422 --> 00:16:02,341
-The money and the plane ticket?
-You'll get it.

144
00:16:02,424 --> 00:16:05,469
But they'll suspect us
if we meet or I pay you now.

145
00:16:05,552 --> 00:16:06,762
Wait until I call you.

146
00:16:09,264 --> 00:16:11,600
POWER OFF

147
00:16:26,281 --> 00:16:28,200
Put some more flowers.

148
00:16:28,742 --> 00:16:29,743
Yes, sir.

149
00:16:36,834 --> 00:16:39,128
How does it feel to be back home?

150
00:16:40,504 --> 00:16:42,339
It doesn't feel like home.

151
00:16:43,757 --> 00:16:45,217
This is your favorite wine.

152
00:16:45,759 --> 00:16:46,969
-Right?
-No thanks.

153
00:16:47,636 --> 00:16:48,470
Are you sure?

154
00:16:49,179 --> 00:16:50,848
The steak is good. Try it.

155
00:16:51,724 --> 00:16:53,350
I don't have an appetite.

156
00:16:54,435 --> 00:16:55,477
You said you were hungry.

157
00:16:55,561 --> 00:16:56,854
I was,

158
00:16:57,521 --> 00:16:59,273
but not anymore.

159
00:16:59,356 --> 00:17:00,524
Let's go now.

160
00:17:02,151 --> 00:17:03,152
Go where?

161
00:17:07,698 --> 00:17:08,949
Give me some time.

162
00:17:09,658 --> 00:17:12,244
-For what?
-So I can clear up the misunderstanding.

163
00:17:12,327 --> 00:17:13,495
What misunderstanding?

164
00:17:15,914 --> 00:17:17,082
You said

165
00:17:17,166 --> 00:17:20,377
that I pushed you
into a ditch only to save you.

166
00:17:21,837 --> 00:17:23,380
But that's not true.

167
00:17:26,550 --> 00:17:27,676
Do you recognize this?

168
00:17:28,510 --> 00:17:29,344
What's that?

169
00:17:30,054 --> 00:17:32,056
It belonged to you a long time ago.

170
00:17:38,729 --> 00:17:40,647
Why do you have it?

171
00:17:50,908 --> 00:17:51,742
Don't tell me…

172
00:17:51,825 --> 00:17:53,952
-That was you?
-It was.

173
00:17:55,537 --> 00:17:58,665
Was that when we first met?

174
00:17:58,749 --> 00:18:01,168
No, it was before that.

175
00:18:02,377 --> 00:18:03,212
Before?

176
00:18:03,962 --> 00:18:04,797
When?

177
00:18:15,641 --> 00:18:18,018
You were the one who saved me?

178
00:18:18,644 --> 00:18:21,105
Yes, I was the one who saved you

179
00:18:21,188 --> 00:18:22,314
from drowning that day.

180
00:18:23,607 --> 00:18:24,566
What are you doing?

181
00:18:26,235 --> 00:18:30,155
I couldn't sleep,
so I was looking at some old albums.

182
00:18:30,239 --> 00:18:31,240
Can I join you?

183
00:18:31,323 --> 00:18:33,617
Of course. Please sit.

184
00:18:38,288 --> 00:18:41,041
Goodness, is this Hyun-woo?

185
00:18:41,792 --> 00:18:42,960
Yes.

186
00:18:45,003 --> 00:18:47,798
Gosh, he was always handsome.

187
00:18:47,881 --> 00:18:51,385
He was. Not everyone knew his name,

188
00:18:51,468 --> 00:18:53,387
but they all knew the cute son

189
00:18:53,470 --> 00:18:54,596
of the pear tree house.

190
00:18:55,430 --> 00:18:58,183
You're blessed
with a handsome and smart son.

191
00:18:58,267 --> 00:19:02,020
Yes. He's good at boxing and swimming too.

192
00:19:02,104 --> 00:19:04,189
Right. Look here.

193
00:19:04,273 --> 00:19:06,483
He even went to
a children's Marine Corps Camp.

194
00:19:06,567 --> 00:19:09,403
He once even saved a kid from drowning.

195
00:19:17,578 --> 00:19:18,579
What is it?

196
00:19:19,538 --> 00:19:20,372
I think

197
00:19:21,331 --> 00:19:24,418
I recognize this beach.

198
00:19:24,501 --> 00:19:26,003
Why were you there?

199
00:19:26,086 --> 00:19:29,131
To see my mother.
That's when I saw you drowning.

200
00:19:29,214 --> 00:19:31,550
-Really?
-Yes.

201
00:19:31,633 --> 00:19:36,263
It was me who met you
and developed feelings for you first.

202
00:19:41,727 --> 00:19:42,728
I didn't know.

203
00:19:44,146 --> 00:19:45,606
You should've told me.

204
00:19:46,773 --> 00:19:50,777
My mother abandoned me
at an orphanage to keep her secret.

205
00:19:50,861 --> 00:19:53,155
So I couldn't say anything.

206
00:19:53,822 --> 00:19:56,200
-It must've been hard.
-It was. So…

207
00:19:58,118 --> 00:19:59,244
eat with me.

208
00:20:00,954 --> 00:20:03,123
I've always wanted to eat with you

209
00:20:03,207 --> 00:20:04,416
at this table.

210
00:20:04,499 --> 00:20:07,878
Hyun-woo reluctantly
ate with you every day.

211
00:20:08,629 --> 00:20:10,547
But this has always been my wish.

212
00:20:13,050 --> 00:20:15,552
So don't look at me that way.

213
00:20:19,014 --> 00:20:19,848
Let's eat.

214
00:20:41,828 --> 00:20:43,497
-Is that really her?
-Gosh.

215
00:20:48,961 --> 00:20:50,921
Let me have some time with him.

216
00:21:20,367 --> 00:21:21,368
Grandfather.

217
00:21:22,327 --> 00:21:23,161
Do you…

218
00:21:24,246 --> 00:21:25,330
recognize me?

219
00:21:31,753 --> 00:21:32,879
Have you gone insane?

220
00:21:32,963 --> 00:21:35,215
How dare you let her in?
Is she in there alone?

221
00:21:36,174 --> 00:21:38,468
-Let her be.
-Are you a saint?

222
00:21:38,552 --> 00:21:40,554
She humiliated you in front of everyone.

223
00:21:41,221 --> 00:21:42,389
Move!

224
00:21:42,472 --> 00:21:44,725
She's with a geezer
who's not in his right mind.

225
00:21:44,808 --> 00:21:46,476
-What could happen?
-Let go.

226
00:21:54,901 --> 00:21:56,862
-Long time no see.
-I guess.

227
00:21:56,945 --> 00:21:58,613
-Has it been a month?
-I heard.

228
00:21:58,697 --> 00:22:01,033
I'm sorry you're sick at such a young age.

229
00:22:01,658 --> 00:22:03,243
That's why I'm visiting my grandfather.

230
00:22:03,327 --> 00:22:05,454
-Because I might die at any time.
-Hae-in.

231
00:22:05,537 --> 00:22:08,373
What are you trying to find out
when you're dying anyway?

232
00:22:08,457 --> 00:22:10,208
What are you afraid I'd find out?

233
00:22:10,959 --> 00:22:14,379
This is exactly why
he entrusted me with everything.

234
00:22:14,463 --> 00:22:17,215
He was afraid his family
would scheme something at times like this

235
00:22:17,299 --> 00:22:19,134
-and only trusted me!
-Talk all you want.

236
00:22:19,217 --> 00:22:21,261
We both know

237
00:22:21,345 --> 00:22:22,888
-that you're lying.
-What?

238
00:22:22,971 --> 00:22:27,100
You only have the power of attorney
as long as he's alive.

239
00:22:27,684 --> 00:22:28,769
So I trust

240
00:22:28,852 --> 00:22:31,730
that you'll take good care of him.

241
00:22:33,940 --> 00:22:36,026
Since when did you even care?

242
00:22:36,109 --> 00:22:38,362
All your family did was fight over money.

243
00:22:39,905 --> 00:22:43,116
I know. But our family suffered
thanks to you,

244
00:22:43,200 --> 00:22:45,994
and now we've become quite close.

245
00:22:46,995 --> 00:22:48,580
But I'm not grateful.

246
00:22:50,415 --> 00:22:51,458
I'll be back soon.

247
00:22:55,796 --> 00:22:57,339
-Don't go.
-Let me go.

248
00:22:57,964 --> 00:22:58,882
What'll you do?

249
00:23:44,594 --> 00:23:46,012
Where's the main gate?

250
00:23:47,264 --> 00:23:48,557
The main gate…

251
00:24:56,708 --> 00:24:57,542
Hae-in.

252
00:25:07,469 --> 00:25:08,303
Are you okay?

253
00:25:11,932 --> 00:25:12,933
What's wrong?

254
00:25:20,857 --> 00:25:21,858
Hyun-woo?

255
00:25:23,527 --> 00:25:24,528
Is that you?

256
00:25:24,611 --> 00:25:26,530
Yes, it's me.

257
00:25:27,739 --> 00:25:28,823
What's the matter?

258
00:25:33,787 --> 00:25:34,704
What happened?

259
00:25:34,788 --> 00:25:36,581
Did you get beaten up again?

260
00:25:42,170 --> 00:25:44,130
How many times must I tell you?

261
00:25:44,214 --> 00:25:46,174
I don't get beaten up.

262
00:25:47,968 --> 00:25:49,761
I can even handle three guys at once.

263
00:26:05,277 --> 00:26:06,987
Seeing how arrogant you are,

264
00:26:08,405 --> 00:26:09,531
you must be Hyun-woo.

265
00:26:31,595 --> 00:26:32,846
Can you excuse me?

266
00:26:41,479 --> 00:26:43,648
What happened?
I thought you got rid of him.

267
00:26:43,732 --> 00:26:46,151
Exactly. You shouldn't have done that.

268
00:26:46,234 --> 00:26:47,193
Done what?

269
00:26:47,277 --> 00:26:49,237
-Come on.
-Check first.

270
00:26:49,321 --> 00:26:51,031
-What?
-You can kill me

271
00:26:51,114 --> 00:26:53,742
after five minutes,
and it won't make a difference.

272
00:26:54,492 --> 00:26:57,120
So call the person
who hired you to kill me

273
00:26:57,203 --> 00:27:00,123
and see if they keep their promise.

274
00:27:13,511 --> 00:27:14,971
I got rid of Mr. Baek.

275
00:27:15,055 --> 00:27:17,140
-Are you sure?
-Yes. What should I do now?

276
00:27:17,223 --> 00:27:18,600
Don't call me and lie low for now.

277
00:27:18,683 --> 00:27:20,602
-The money and the plane ticket?
-You'll get it.

278
00:27:20,685 --> 00:27:23,146
But they'll suspect us
if we meet or I pay you now.

279
00:27:23,229 --> 00:27:24,564
Wait until I call you.

280
00:27:24,648 --> 00:27:26,274
Hello? Wait, listen--

281
00:27:27,275 --> 00:27:28,109
Damn it.

282
00:27:29,027 --> 00:27:29,944
MR. YOON EUN-SUNG 2

283
00:27:30,820 --> 00:27:33,698
The number you have dialed is unavailable…

284
00:27:33,782 --> 00:27:36,368
This asshole.

285
00:27:41,790 --> 00:27:44,376
You're just a real estate scammer for now.

286
00:27:44,459 --> 00:27:46,211
But you'll become a killer
once you kill me.

287
00:27:46,294 --> 00:27:47,754
Don't pull one on me.

288
00:27:47,837 --> 00:27:50,799
The police are still investigating
your assault case on me.

289
00:27:50,882 --> 00:27:54,094
But if I die, that case
will turn into attempted murder.

290
00:27:54,177 --> 00:27:56,096
You'll become a suspect

291
00:27:56,179 --> 00:27:58,306
and get additional punishment
for planning it.

292
00:27:58,390 --> 00:28:00,517
Then Interpol will put you
on their Red Notice,

293
00:28:00,600 --> 00:28:02,060
their highest wanted list.

294
00:28:03,144 --> 00:28:04,729
I told you to shut up.

295
00:28:05,980 --> 00:28:10,235
You'll get at least 20 years for planning
a revenge killing and fleeing.

296
00:28:10,318 --> 00:28:12,946
But if you don't kill me,

297
00:28:13,822 --> 00:28:16,324
you'll only get three years for the fraud.

298
00:28:16,408 --> 00:28:20,412
You could even get probation if I convince
the landowners to settle the case.

299
00:28:21,037 --> 00:28:24,124
So? I'll put everything aside
if you stop here.

300
00:28:24,207 --> 00:28:26,209
So you just let him go?

301
00:28:26,292 --> 00:28:28,336
-Are you stupid?
-Yes, I was.

302
00:28:28,420 --> 00:28:29,629
Pay me right now.

303
00:28:29,713 --> 00:28:33,258
Or I'll tell the police
that it was you who hired me.

304
00:28:42,183 --> 00:28:44,519
This is where I've been staying.

305
00:29:03,621 --> 00:29:04,873
Gosh, you startled me!

306
00:29:10,545 --> 00:29:11,755
It's okay. Don't clean up.

307
00:29:11,838 --> 00:29:13,882
I've just been too busy.

308
00:29:17,552 --> 00:29:20,054
I wondered where you were staying
after the divorce.

309
00:29:20,805 --> 00:29:21,806
You were here.

310
00:29:23,016 --> 00:29:23,850
Well…

311
00:29:25,143 --> 00:29:26,644
Has it been uncomfortable?

312
00:29:28,354 --> 00:29:29,189
Well…

313
00:29:30,440 --> 00:29:32,317
No, it's a good place.

314
00:29:33,359 --> 00:29:35,403
It was newly built and fully furnished.

315
00:29:47,582 --> 00:29:49,250
Why did you sleep on the sofa?

316
00:29:49,334 --> 00:29:50,502
Well…

317
00:29:52,128 --> 00:29:53,922
You know I sleep well.

318
00:29:54,714 --> 00:29:57,008
I can sleep

319
00:29:57,801 --> 00:29:59,260
wherever I put my head down.

320
00:30:00,470 --> 00:30:03,223
I guess you could sleep well

321
00:30:03,306 --> 00:30:05,517
after our divorce, unlike me.

322
00:30:06,351 --> 00:30:08,228
-What?
-It was your dream to get a divorce.

323
00:30:08,311 --> 00:30:11,648
Now that it's come true,
you must've found peace

324
00:30:11,731 --> 00:30:13,733
in this newly built
and fully furnished place.

325
00:30:13,817 --> 00:30:15,735
That's not what I meant.

326
00:30:15,819 --> 00:30:18,822
It's okay. At least one of us
was happy after the divorce.

327
00:30:18,905 --> 00:30:19,781
I'm glad.

328
00:30:23,493 --> 00:30:25,829
I wasn't comfortable at all.

329
00:30:25,912 --> 00:30:29,958
This place gave me sick building syndrome,
so I suffered from headaches.

330
00:30:30,041 --> 00:30:34,128
And look. The living room
is right next to the kitchen,

331
00:30:34,212 --> 00:30:37,131
so it's not easy to air this place out.

332
00:30:37,215 --> 00:30:38,049
And most of all,

333
00:30:40,009 --> 00:30:40,844
you're not here.

334
00:30:47,976 --> 00:30:49,310
Isn't that better for you?

335
00:30:49,394 --> 00:30:50,436
Not at all.

336
00:30:50,520 --> 00:30:53,064
At times, I wondered how it would feel

337
00:30:53,773 --> 00:30:55,900
if we had lived here as newlyweds.

338
00:30:56,860 --> 00:30:59,946
It would've been nice to live
in a small place like this

339
00:31:01,114 --> 00:31:03,783
even after arguing with each other.

340
00:31:08,788 --> 00:31:10,999
My mind would wander like that,

341
00:31:12,250 --> 00:31:13,585
and I'd miss you.

342
00:31:15,461 --> 00:31:16,546
I did.

343
00:31:25,263 --> 00:31:26,097
I'm hungry.

344
00:31:26,180 --> 00:31:29,893
Really? I'll cook you something.
Get some rest.

345
00:32:51,724 --> 00:32:52,725
This looks good.

346
00:32:52,809 --> 00:32:54,143
Let's eat.

347
00:33:09,325 --> 00:33:10,576
You're really good.

348
00:33:11,494 --> 00:33:12,954
Why didn't you ever cook?

349
00:33:13,788 --> 00:33:14,956
I never had the chance.

350
00:33:23,381 --> 00:33:24,799
By the way…

351
00:33:24,882 --> 00:33:26,718
Will you see other women after I die?

352
00:33:30,638 --> 00:33:31,639
What?

353
00:33:31,723 --> 00:33:35,351
Will you live with someone
in this small place even after arguing?

354
00:33:35,435 --> 00:33:38,479
Will you make her stew and live happily…

355
00:33:39,355 --> 00:33:40,440
ever after?

356
00:33:42,025 --> 00:33:43,192
What are you saying?

357
00:33:44,318 --> 00:33:45,361
Just eat.

358
00:33:47,155 --> 00:33:48,364
Answer me.

359
00:33:49,032 --> 00:33:50,575
Don't change the subject again.

360
00:33:50,658 --> 00:33:52,410
Do you want to die before me?

361
00:33:52,493 --> 00:33:54,037
You worry too much.

362
00:33:54,120 --> 00:33:55,496
Who would want to date me?

363
00:33:55,580 --> 00:33:59,375
Everyone thinks you saved me,
because you're helplessly in love.

364
00:33:59,459 --> 00:34:01,586
They're also criticizing me
for not knowing that

365
00:34:01,669 --> 00:34:03,337
and leaving you.

366
00:34:03,421 --> 00:34:04,797
So what kind of woman--

367
00:34:04,881 --> 00:34:07,341
What kind of woman
wouldn't want to date you?

368
00:34:09,302 --> 00:34:11,304
You're handsome, kind,

369
00:34:11,888 --> 00:34:13,890
smart, but not arrogant.

370
00:34:13,973 --> 00:34:16,601
Plus, you're a good cook.

371
00:34:17,935 --> 00:34:19,187
There's no man like you.

372
00:34:20,438 --> 00:34:23,566
Even if I was reborn a hundred times,
I'd still marry you

373
00:34:23,649 --> 00:34:24,859
every single time.

374
00:34:36,871 --> 00:34:39,207
How could you say such a thing

375
00:34:39,290 --> 00:34:40,708
without even blinking…

376
00:34:42,502 --> 00:34:43,503
your eyes?

377
00:34:44,087 --> 00:34:45,004
It's true.

378
00:34:46,380 --> 00:34:47,673
So why would I hesitate?

379
00:34:50,927 --> 00:34:54,514
You know how to make my heart race.

380
00:35:18,412 --> 00:35:19,831
Do you finally get it?

381
00:35:21,082 --> 00:35:23,000
Hae-in doesn't care about you.

382
00:35:23,084 --> 00:35:24,794
She's always using you.

383
00:35:24,877 --> 00:35:26,504
I've always known that.

384
00:35:27,338 --> 00:35:29,298
-Yet you still let her?
-Yes.

385
00:35:30,341 --> 00:35:31,175
It's a habit.

386
00:35:33,511 --> 00:35:34,804
I was always used

387
00:35:35,763 --> 00:35:36,681
by you too.

388
00:35:45,731 --> 00:35:49,861
You resent me
for abandoning you abroad, don't you?

389
00:35:51,279 --> 00:35:54,699
Do you think I didn't know
that your adoptive parents abused you

390
00:35:54,782 --> 00:35:57,160
despite getting paid handsomely?

391
00:35:57,785 --> 00:35:59,162
Was it a coincidence

392
00:35:59,245 --> 00:36:01,622
that those nondrinkers died
while driving drunk?

393
00:36:02,874 --> 00:36:04,041
What are you saying?

394
00:36:06,002 --> 00:36:08,629
What about the orphanage director
who mistreated you?

395
00:36:08,713 --> 00:36:13,009
They closed down due to
a sudden fire, and the director died.

396
00:36:14,635 --> 00:36:15,970
Was that a coincidence?

397
00:36:21,267 --> 00:36:22,768
I never neglected you.

398
00:36:22,852 --> 00:36:26,731
I didn't just sit on my hands
when those people caused you pain

399
00:36:26,814 --> 00:36:28,232
or got in your way.

400
00:36:28,941 --> 00:36:30,109
And that hasn't changed.

401
00:36:30,193 --> 00:36:31,986
Being the chairman isn't enough.

402
00:36:32,069 --> 00:36:35,448
It's my goal to make everything yours.

403
00:36:36,115 --> 00:36:37,617
And I won't sit still

404
00:36:39,160 --> 00:36:40,453
if anyone gets in my way

405
00:36:41,245 --> 00:36:42,997
whether it's Hae-in or someone else.

406
00:36:44,207 --> 00:36:46,876
Do you understand?
This is my way of loving you.

407
00:36:50,630 --> 00:36:52,215
If you truly love her

408
00:36:52,882 --> 00:36:55,468
and don't want her to get hurt,

409
00:36:57,178 --> 00:37:01,098
then don't let her use you.
I won't stand for it.

410
00:37:05,394 --> 00:37:06,354
Come on.

411
00:37:06,437 --> 00:37:08,272
How could you get hurt again?

412
00:37:10,399 --> 00:37:11,359
What happened?

413
00:37:11,442 --> 00:37:13,569
I already told you.

414
00:37:14,362 --> 00:37:16,322
It was a minor car accident.

415
00:37:17,031 --> 00:37:19,992
My mind wasn't all there
when I was driving.

416
00:37:20,618 --> 00:37:22,870
Right, did you get to see
your grandfather?

417
00:37:24,330 --> 00:37:26,582
Grandfather, do you recognize me?

418
00:37:30,419 --> 00:37:33,547
Lady, I'm hungry.

419
00:37:38,636 --> 00:37:39,637
Grandfather…

420
00:37:46,644 --> 00:37:47,603
Have you gone insane?

421
00:37:47,687 --> 00:37:49,272
-How dare you let her in?
-Grandfather.

422
00:37:49,355 --> 00:37:51,148
-I have no time.
-Is she in there alone?

423
00:37:51,816 --> 00:37:52,858
Let her be.

424
00:37:52,942 --> 00:37:54,443
Are you a saint?

425
00:37:54,527 --> 00:37:55,736
She humiliated you…

426
00:37:55,820 --> 00:37:58,322
Do you remember this pen?

427
00:37:58,406 --> 00:37:59,615
You gifted it to me.

428
00:38:00,574 --> 00:38:02,952
You even engraved my initials on it.

429
00:38:03,035 --> 00:38:04,578
It can record sounds.

430
00:38:13,838 --> 00:38:15,172
I'll place it over there,

431
00:38:15,256 --> 00:38:17,717
so if you have anything to say, record it.

432
00:38:18,426 --> 00:38:19,844
I'll be back soon.

433
00:38:20,469 --> 00:38:22,471
He'll recognize the pen once he comes

434
00:38:22,555 --> 00:38:23,597
to his senses.

435
00:38:23,681 --> 00:38:25,891
He got it custom-made and gifted it to me

436
00:38:25,975 --> 00:38:27,310
when I became the CEO.

437
00:38:27,393 --> 00:38:28,853
It's something only we know.

438
00:38:34,734 --> 00:38:36,527
What did Hae-in say?

439
00:38:36,610 --> 00:38:38,863
I bet she asked about the secret fund.

440
00:38:40,114 --> 00:38:42,700
Why did you have to hide it
and make us all suffer?

441
00:38:42,783 --> 00:38:46,120
You should've wired it to me
if that was your plan all along.

442
00:38:47,079 --> 00:38:49,165
What'll you do?
Take it with you when you die?

443
00:38:49,248 --> 00:38:50,499
You fool.

444
00:38:50,583 --> 00:38:54,587
You can't die. You're only barely alive
because of that damn money!

445
00:39:09,810 --> 00:39:11,312
Are you sure you're out of it?

446
00:39:11,395 --> 00:39:12,813
Did Hae-in tell you?

447
00:39:12,897 --> 00:39:15,274
She's dying soon.

448
00:39:15,983 --> 00:39:18,652
She has a rare case of a brain tumor
and won't live long.

449
00:39:20,446 --> 00:39:22,865
Look at what happened
to the great Hong Man-dae.

450
00:39:23,949 --> 00:39:26,994
You can't even process the fact
that your favorite granddaughter is dying.

451
00:39:27,078 --> 00:39:28,204
Serves you right.

452
00:39:56,899 --> 00:39:58,609
I'm strong.

453
00:39:58,692 --> 00:40:00,194
I'm the best.

454
00:40:00,277 --> 00:40:02,696
I'm a lunatic.

455
00:40:02,780 --> 00:40:05,908
I'm a total lunatic. I'm--

456
00:40:13,249 --> 00:40:15,626
I'm a strong male--

457
00:40:25,719 --> 00:40:27,221
When did you get here?

458
00:40:27,304 --> 00:40:29,765
I came after my morning jog.

459
00:40:31,225 --> 00:40:33,519
You remind me of myself
when I first started boxing.

460
00:40:33,602 --> 00:40:34,854
I like this attitude of yours.

461
00:40:38,232 --> 00:40:39,567
Where are you coming from?

462
00:40:39,650 --> 00:40:41,402
I dropped Ho-yeol off at school.

463
00:40:41,485 --> 00:40:42,486
I see.

464
00:40:43,904 --> 00:40:45,156
By the way,

465
00:40:46,407 --> 00:40:48,534
does your wife work somewhere far away?

466
00:40:48,617 --> 00:40:50,953
-Do you only meet on the weekends?
-No, we live together.

467
00:40:51,036 --> 00:40:52,913
I see. I just never met her.

468
00:40:52,997 --> 00:40:54,206
You see…

469
00:40:54,290 --> 00:40:56,375
When we first got married,

470
00:40:56,459 --> 00:40:59,211
my mom told her this.
"You're my daughter-in-law."

471
00:40:59,295 --> 00:41:00,921
You're not my daughter.

472
00:41:01,005 --> 00:41:03,090
A daughter-in-law can't be a daughter.

473
00:41:03,174 --> 00:41:05,050
I hit Mi-seon.

474
00:41:05,134 --> 00:41:06,510
Come on.

475
00:41:07,386 --> 00:41:10,639
But you have your own parents,
and I can't do that to you.

476
00:41:10,723 --> 00:41:14,018
We should watch what we say
and never get physical

477
00:41:14,101 --> 00:41:15,227
if we're in-laws.

478
00:41:15,311 --> 00:41:16,729
Yes, you're right.

479
00:41:16,812 --> 00:41:18,564
So now that you're married,

480
00:41:18,647 --> 00:41:20,232
-let's avoid seeing each other.
-What?

481
00:41:20,316 --> 00:41:21,275
Seriously?

482
00:41:21,358 --> 00:41:26,071
You can visit your parents or go on a trip
during national holidays if you want.

483
00:41:26,155 --> 00:41:27,490
Thank you.

484
00:41:27,573 --> 00:41:30,409
And don't bother
getting me birthday gifts.

485
00:41:30,493 --> 00:41:33,287
It's uncomfortable.
If you want, just text me an emoji.

486
00:41:35,372 --> 00:41:38,834
Don't you think that's too little?

487
00:41:38,918 --> 00:41:41,754
Shut up. However, I have one condition.

488
00:41:41,837 --> 00:41:44,215
My son has many flaws,

489
00:41:44,298 --> 00:41:45,966
and there's nothing I can do.

490
00:41:46,050 --> 00:41:48,761
You can try to fix him,
but don't return him to me.

491
00:41:48,844 --> 00:41:49,929
Come on, Mom.

492
00:41:55,184 --> 00:41:57,186
I'll do my best.

493
00:41:58,729 --> 00:42:00,981
Your mother is so laid-back.

494
00:42:01,065 --> 00:42:03,526
Thanks to her,
my wife's colleagues all say

495
00:42:03,609 --> 00:42:05,319
that she has the best mother-in-law.

496
00:42:05,402 --> 00:42:07,071
I can see that.

497
00:42:07,154 --> 00:42:08,656
Since my mom treats her well,

498
00:42:08,739 --> 00:42:11,951
my wife tends
to turn a blind eye to most things

499
00:42:12,034 --> 00:42:13,244
that I do.

500
00:42:14,036 --> 00:42:15,162
That's how we live.

501
00:42:20,918 --> 00:42:22,336
Hey…

502
00:42:23,087 --> 00:42:25,089
-I didn't mean to brag.
-But you did.

503
00:42:25,172 --> 00:42:26,674
I didn't mean to.

504
00:42:28,384 --> 00:42:30,302
Are you sulking? Soo-cheol.

505
00:42:30,386 --> 00:42:31,512
Damn it.

506
00:42:34,890 --> 00:42:35,766
This is it?

507
00:42:35,849 --> 00:42:39,520
I know you stole all their pricey artwork

508
00:42:39,603 --> 00:42:41,355
-before leaving.
-No, I didn't.

509
00:42:41,438 --> 00:42:43,023
I just grabbed a few.

510
00:42:43,107 --> 00:42:44,233
Then I bought an apartment.

511
00:42:44,316 --> 00:42:47,570
I know you stole
a golden Buddha statue this big.

512
00:42:47,653 --> 00:42:49,280
No, I didn't.

513
00:42:49,363 --> 00:42:51,490
You're not fooling me.

514
00:43:05,796 --> 00:43:07,131
Geon-u, are you okay?

515
00:43:09,466 --> 00:43:10,884
Hey, what are you doing?

516
00:43:12,428 --> 00:43:14,805
I see. So he's your weakness.

517
00:43:16,974 --> 00:43:17,850
Are you crazy?

518
00:43:17,933 --> 00:43:19,935
Touch him, and you're dead.

519
00:43:20,019 --> 00:43:21,562
Where is the statue?

520
00:43:22,938 --> 00:43:24,773
I know you haven't sold it.

521
00:43:24,857 --> 00:43:27,693
I already looked into it,
so don't lie to me.

522
00:43:33,324 --> 00:43:34,658
It's in a private safe.

523
00:43:36,076 --> 00:43:37,578
We'll go there tomorrow morning.

524
00:43:39,955 --> 00:43:42,541
Okay. Good.

525
00:43:42,625 --> 00:43:43,667
Good girl.

526
00:43:47,338 --> 00:43:50,049
Hey, pour me some wine. Okay?

527
00:45:54,173 --> 00:45:55,382
Did you sleep well?

528
00:45:56,008 --> 00:45:57,009
Yes.

529
00:45:59,178 --> 00:46:00,179
I like this place.

530
00:46:01,388 --> 00:46:04,057
I fell asleep right away just like you.

531
00:46:08,312 --> 00:46:09,354
I told you.

532
00:46:10,314 --> 00:46:11,732
Do you want to sleep more?

533
00:46:11,815 --> 00:46:12,691
No.

534
00:46:17,946 --> 00:46:19,740
Give me ten minutes.

535
00:46:22,826 --> 00:46:24,453
No, just five.

536
00:46:55,108 --> 00:46:57,152
We haven't had
a nice breakfast in a while.

537
00:46:57,236 --> 00:46:59,696
I should have some salad and coffee.

538
00:47:00,906 --> 00:47:03,492
Hyun-woo sneaked in here last night.

539
00:47:03,575 --> 00:47:04,409
What?

540
00:47:05,369 --> 00:47:06,954
Goodness. How?

541
00:47:07,037 --> 00:47:09,998
He knew the back gate's camera was broken
and came in through there.

542
00:47:10,082 --> 00:47:10,916
I see.

543
00:47:11,834 --> 00:47:14,545
-He's so smart and thorough.
-Not at all.

544
00:47:14,628 --> 00:47:17,923
He didn't erase the dashcam footage
in the other car.

545
00:47:20,801 --> 00:47:22,302
So I found out how he got in.

546
00:47:35,274 --> 00:47:37,568
Why are you putting me in a pickle?

547
00:47:38,402 --> 00:47:40,070
Have you forgotten who I am?

548
00:47:40,153 --> 00:47:43,323
You're the defected heroine
who joined our side.

549
00:47:43,407 --> 00:47:46,368
No. Keep this up, and I'm going back.

550
00:47:46,451 --> 00:47:49,580
Ms. Moh will kill me if she finds out.

551
00:47:50,789 --> 00:47:52,875
I'm close to locating the secret fund.

552
00:47:53,876 --> 00:47:56,003
That's why Hae-in came here.

553
00:47:57,421 --> 00:47:59,256
God, this is driving me insane.

554
00:48:00,507 --> 00:48:02,509
Give me 3% of the money then.

555
00:48:02,593 --> 00:48:03,719
Make that 5%.

556
00:48:04,761 --> 00:48:05,679
Do you mean that?

557
00:48:05,762 --> 00:48:09,975
I betrayed them,
and they're still livid about it.

558
00:48:10,601 --> 00:48:12,436
Of course. You can trust me.

559
00:48:14,771 --> 00:48:15,856
Don't smile at me.

560
00:48:15,939 --> 00:48:18,775
Handsome men are dangerous.

561
00:48:29,494 --> 00:48:31,163
Seul-hee is going to kill me.

562
00:48:31,747 --> 00:48:32,623
Thank you.

563
00:48:33,874 --> 00:48:34,833
I forgave you once,

564
00:48:34,917 --> 00:48:37,544
so how dare you
side with them again like a rat?

565
00:48:37,628 --> 00:48:40,797
Dogs can be pets, but not rats.

566
00:48:40,881 --> 00:48:43,258
They need to be killed at all costs.

567
00:48:43,884 --> 00:48:47,346
Return your car pass, ID card,
and company card before you leave.

568
00:48:48,347 --> 00:48:51,767
Your greed could cost you
all the money you have, Grace.

569
00:48:51,850 --> 00:48:54,811
It would be best
to lie low for your safety.

570
00:48:54,895 --> 00:48:55,938
-Ms. Moh.
-Get lost.

571
00:48:56,021 --> 00:48:57,481
No, I can't do that.

572
00:48:57,564 --> 00:49:00,609
How can I
when there's a huge misunderstanding?

573
00:49:00,692 --> 00:49:04,237
I make a living out of information,
and people often mistake me for a rat.

574
00:49:04,321 --> 00:49:05,405
But what can I do?

575
00:49:05,489 --> 00:49:07,199
That's just who I am.

576
00:49:10,369 --> 00:49:11,370
A misunderstanding?

577
00:49:11,453 --> 00:49:14,373
Then explain why
you brought Hyun-woo of all people

578
00:49:15,040 --> 00:49:15,874
to my house.

579
00:49:17,376 --> 00:49:20,545
Hyun-woo offered me a deal.

580
00:49:20,629 --> 00:49:22,714
He offered to give me
10% of the secret fund.

581
00:49:23,840 --> 00:49:26,093
So he knows where the money is?

582
00:49:26,176 --> 00:49:27,844
That's what I was curious about.

583
00:49:27,928 --> 00:49:29,346
So I agreed to help.

584
00:49:29,429 --> 00:49:30,472
And where is it?

585
00:49:31,682 --> 00:49:35,686
Hyun-woo offered 10%,
but I'm fine with 7% from you.

586
00:49:37,270 --> 00:49:38,230
Don't mess with me.

587
00:49:40,190 --> 00:49:42,234
Then a small building and just 5%.

588
00:49:42,317 --> 00:49:44,695
I deserve that much.

589
00:49:49,533 --> 00:49:50,617
Tell me.

590
00:49:54,121 --> 00:49:55,539
He thinks

591
00:49:55,622 --> 00:49:57,082
it's in this house.

592
00:50:09,761 --> 00:50:11,346
-Could I be wrong?
-What?

593
00:50:11,430 --> 00:50:14,391
I see some men
taking photos of me behind that wall.

594
00:50:14,474 --> 00:50:15,976
Jeez.

595
00:50:16,476 --> 00:50:18,353
I can't believe this.

596
00:50:18,437 --> 00:50:19,813
I still got it, don't I?

597
00:50:19,896 --> 00:50:21,398
-Let them be.
-Why?

598
00:50:21,481 --> 00:50:23,734
They'll leave in a bit.

599
00:50:27,404 --> 00:50:28,405
Did they leave?

600
00:50:30,490 --> 00:50:31,324
Bang-sil.

601
00:50:31,992 --> 00:50:34,369
They left.
You don't have to suck it in anymore.

602
00:50:34,453 --> 00:50:35,412
There you go.

603
00:50:35,495 --> 00:50:37,789
I think I saw them

604
00:50:37,873 --> 00:50:40,042
-yesterday as well.
-What?

605
00:50:40,125 --> 00:50:42,377
They kept coming by in a black van.

606
00:50:42,461 --> 00:50:45,255
They keep taking photos of things.

607
00:50:47,591 --> 00:50:49,009
Where did I put my pricey heels?

608
00:50:54,765 --> 00:50:56,099
Hey.

609
00:50:56,183 --> 00:50:57,476
We need to talk.

610
00:51:00,395 --> 00:51:01,313
What do you want?

611
00:51:01,396 --> 00:51:03,398
You took a photo of our house?
Give me your camera.

612
00:51:03,482 --> 00:51:06,151
-We didn't take anything. Let's go.
-I saw you.

613
00:51:06,234 --> 00:51:07,569
So give it to me!

614
00:51:07,652 --> 00:51:09,029
Goodness.

615
00:51:09,696 --> 00:51:10,989
Hey, are you crazy?

616
00:51:11,073 --> 00:51:12,157
Hey.

617
00:51:13,575 --> 00:51:16,369
-You hit me first.
-Yes. So what?

618
00:51:16,453 --> 00:51:18,622
Do you know what kind of heels I have on?

619
00:51:20,499 --> 00:51:24,211
They had poop on them,
and I'll trample you with them!

620
00:51:30,884 --> 00:51:32,260
You scumbags!

621
00:51:42,562 --> 00:51:43,563
Gosh, that hurts.

622
00:51:44,397 --> 00:51:46,274
Hey, what are you guys doing there?

623
00:51:46,358 --> 00:51:48,068
-Dad…
-What are you doing?

624
00:51:48,735 --> 00:51:49,694
Help us…

625
00:51:50,654 --> 00:51:52,030
Ready, set, go.

626
00:51:52,614 --> 00:51:54,241
Cross. That's it. Cross.

627
00:51:54,324 --> 00:51:56,118
Cross.

628
00:51:56,201 --> 00:52:00,163
One leg.

629
00:52:00,247 --> 00:52:01,540
Cross. That's it. Cross.

630
00:52:01,623 --> 00:52:02,541
Yes. Cross.

631
00:52:02,624 --> 00:52:04,543
One leg.

632
00:52:04,626 --> 00:52:05,669
-Jump.
-Did you hear?

633
00:52:05,752 --> 00:52:06,586
Jump! What?

634
00:52:06,670 --> 00:52:08,839
-They're forming a Yongdu-ri Quintet.
-Right.

635
00:52:08,922 --> 00:52:11,758
You mean the village patrol team?
I heard about the mysterious van.

636
00:52:11,842 --> 00:52:12,676
Exactly.

637
00:52:13,760 --> 00:52:15,011
Keep going. Repeat.

638
00:52:16,096 --> 00:52:17,722
I'm going to sign up.

639
00:52:17,806 --> 00:52:20,475
I've quickly grown some muscles too.
I bulked up. Touch it.

640
00:52:20,559 --> 00:52:21,935
No thanks.

641
00:52:23,061 --> 00:52:25,397
Quintet means they'll pick five people.

642
00:52:25,480 --> 00:52:29,109
Being a part of it means I'll be
one of the five strongest men here.

643
00:52:29,192 --> 00:52:32,529
Do you think I can make it?
I want to punch something and break it.

644
00:52:32,612 --> 00:52:35,365
Do you suggest a wooden bar or roof tiles?

645
00:52:35,448 --> 00:52:36,283
Soo-cheol--

646
00:52:36,366 --> 00:52:37,993
I know it won't be easy.

647
00:52:38,076 --> 00:52:40,537
But I had a good dream last night.

648
00:52:41,413 --> 00:52:42,247
I'm feeling hopeful.

649
00:52:42,330 --> 00:52:43,999
There'll be less than five participants.

650
00:52:52,299 --> 00:52:53,383
All right.

651
00:52:53,466 --> 00:52:54,885
We're done then.

652
00:52:54,968 --> 00:52:56,303
It'll be us five.

653
00:52:57,512 --> 00:52:59,347
Leave me out of this.

654
00:52:59,431 --> 00:53:01,308
I just stepped down from office.

655
00:53:01,391 --> 00:53:04,269
People might interpret it politically

656
00:53:04,352 --> 00:53:07,147
if they find out I formed a private group.

657
00:53:07,230 --> 00:53:11,401
It'll only spark a conflict
between the two parties.

658
00:53:11,484 --> 00:53:14,237
I can't leave my mom's side either.

659
00:53:15,447 --> 00:53:18,241
You always leave her unattended
when you drink.

660
00:53:18,325 --> 00:53:22,495
-Why are you pretending to be a good son?
-Come on, guys.

661
00:53:22,579 --> 00:53:24,623
We need at least five members

662
00:53:24,706 --> 00:53:27,876
if we want this group to be funded.

663
00:53:27,959 --> 00:53:28,793
Does this mean

664
00:53:30,128 --> 00:53:31,463
I'm in?

665
00:53:31,963 --> 00:53:33,548
Yes, it does.

666
00:53:34,674 --> 00:53:35,884
I can punch this.

667
00:53:35,967 --> 00:53:36,927
That's okay.

668
00:53:37,010 --> 00:53:39,387
Becoming one of us means
it'll be permanent.

669
00:53:39,471 --> 00:53:40,972
You can't back out later.

670
00:53:41,973 --> 00:53:43,225
See?

671
00:53:43,308 --> 00:53:45,685
I told you you didn't have to try much.

672
00:54:09,125 --> 00:54:09,960
Are we almost there?

673
00:54:10,043 --> 00:54:11,086
Yes.

674
00:54:11,169 --> 00:54:12,170
Almost.

675
00:54:13,505 --> 00:54:14,631
Shall we get out?

676
00:54:31,523 --> 00:54:32,357
This is nice.

677
00:54:33,066 --> 00:54:36,152
Everyone confesses their feelings here,

678
00:54:36,236 --> 00:54:38,530
and no one has failed so far.

679
00:54:39,739 --> 00:54:42,993
Your love comes true
if you confess it here.

680
00:54:43,076 --> 00:54:46,329
And it's worked every time.

681
00:54:47,205 --> 00:54:48,123
That's absurd.

682
00:54:50,125 --> 00:54:52,043
Not only do you get

683
00:54:52,127 --> 00:54:54,087
a beautiful sunset,

684
00:54:55,297 --> 00:54:59,342
but the light also gives your face
a warm tone,

685
00:54:59,426 --> 00:55:01,177
which makes you look more gorgeous.

686
00:55:01,261 --> 00:55:03,305
You look beautiful

687
00:55:03,930 --> 00:55:04,931
right now.

688
00:55:05,015 --> 00:55:06,141
Is that so?

689
00:55:07,225 --> 00:55:09,060
So will you confess your love?

690
00:55:12,689 --> 00:55:14,232
It's actually more

691
00:55:15,275 --> 00:55:16,276
of a request.

692
00:55:17,819 --> 00:55:18,820
What kind?

693
00:55:29,789 --> 00:55:32,292
A divorce withdrawal.

694
00:55:35,879 --> 00:55:38,465
Asking you to marry me again
would be too much.

695
00:55:39,132 --> 00:55:41,843
So could you at least
take back the divorce?

696
00:55:57,317 --> 00:55:58,735
You remembered my size.

697
00:56:00,653 --> 00:56:01,821
Of course.

698
00:56:03,281 --> 00:56:05,617
But I should put that on you.

699
00:56:19,964 --> 00:56:20,965
Get a refund.

700
00:56:25,887 --> 00:56:26,721
Why?

701
00:56:28,098 --> 00:56:30,725
You said you wanted to
marry me every single time.

702
00:56:31,476 --> 00:56:34,020
That's if I was reborn, but not now.

703
00:56:36,564 --> 00:56:38,983
Why not exactly?

704
00:56:40,026 --> 00:56:40,902
Why?

705
00:56:48,284 --> 00:56:49,577
Yesterday, I thought…

706
00:56:54,874 --> 00:56:55,959
it was you.

707
00:56:58,044 --> 00:56:59,212
-What?
-I…

708
00:57:00,171 --> 00:57:01,297
followed Eun-sung

709
00:57:02,841 --> 00:57:04,300
because I thought it was you.

710
00:57:07,178 --> 00:57:08,471
It has come this far.

711
00:57:09,222 --> 00:57:11,057
My memory is unstable.

712
00:57:11,141 --> 00:57:13,059
I forgot where I was.

713
00:57:14,269 --> 00:57:17,355
And in the end,
I couldn't even recognize you.

714
00:57:34,497 --> 00:57:35,373
Hyun-woo?

715
00:58:01,191 --> 00:58:02,025
I told you

716
00:58:03,401 --> 00:58:04,777
that we shouldn't be together

717
00:58:05,320 --> 00:58:06,571
if my illness worsens.

718
00:58:08,323 --> 00:58:09,365
But…

719
00:58:10,700 --> 00:58:12,202
that time came sooner than expected.

720
00:58:17,749 --> 00:58:19,250
The sunset is beautiful.

721
00:58:20,293 --> 00:58:21,127
You're right.

722
00:58:22,587 --> 00:58:24,130
The sunlight

723
00:58:24,839 --> 00:58:27,217
makes you look more handsome.

724
00:58:30,678 --> 00:58:31,513
But…

725
00:58:34,891 --> 00:58:37,352
are you even really Baek Hyun-woo?

726
00:58:42,732 --> 00:58:44,734
Is this real? Am I not dreaming?

727
00:58:48,404 --> 00:58:50,365
I can't be sure of anything anymore.

728
00:58:54,494 --> 00:58:56,538
That's why I can't make any promises.

729
00:58:57,163 --> 00:58:57,997
I'm sorry.

730
00:59:53,428 --> 00:59:54,971
What's that in his hand?

731
00:59:55,054 --> 00:59:56,598
The curtain is in the way.

732
00:59:56,681 --> 00:59:59,183
It has low resolution.
Should I get a higher one?

733
01:00:04,897 --> 01:00:06,441
Have you seen my mother?

734
01:00:06,524 --> 01:00:07,900
No, I haven't.

735
01:00:09,902 --> 01:00:12,363
You're not lying, are you? I'm serious.

736
01:00:13,281 --> 01:00:14,449
What is he saying?

737
01:00:14,532 --> 01:00:15,533
I'm serious too.

738
01:00:16,242 --> 01:00:17,619
Hey! Yeong-song!

739
01:00:18,494 --> 01:00:20,204
-Have you found her?
-No.

740
01:00:20,288 --> 01:00:21,581
She wasn't in town either.

741
01:00:21,664 --> 01:00:23,833
We should call the police.

742
01:00:23,916 --> 01:00:24,917
I already did.

743
01:00:25,001 --> 01:00:26,002
Good job.

744
01:00:26,085 --> 01:00:29,505
You don't think
she's in the mountains again, do you?

745
01:00:29,589 --> 01:00:32,216
-Goodness.
-The sun will set soon.

746
01:00:32,300 --> 01:00:33,343
I'll check.

747
01:00:33,426 --> 01:00:34,302
Wait.

748
01:00:36,095 --> 01:00:38,806
I think I can help.

749
01:00:48,232 --> 01:00:49,567
There it goes.

750
01:00:51,027 --> 01:00:52,320
A bit more to the right.

751
01:00:52,403 --> 01:00:54,364
A bit more,
and you'll see the mineral springs.

752
01:00:54,447 --> 01:00:56,240
A bit more. Yes, there.

753
01:00:56,324 --> 01:00:58,868
Go up from there.

754
01:00:58,951 --> 01:01:00,620
More.

755
01:01:00,703 --> 01:01:02,163
Keep going.

756
01:01:05,875 --> 01:01:07,919
There's a peak called the Fairy Peak.

757
01:01:11,255 --> 01:01:12,632
That's it!

758
01:01:23,142 --> 01:01:24,227
There she is!

759
01:01:35,196 --> 01:01:36,030
Mom!

760
01:01:37,949 --> 01:01:38,783
Mom!

761
01:01:44,706 --> 01:01:46,124
-Is she asleep?
-Yes.

762
01:01:47,166 --> 01:01:49,001
Thank you so much.

763
01:01:50,420 --> 01:01:51,421
I'm jealous.

764
01:01:51,504 --> 01:01:52,463
Of what?

765
01:01:53,131 --> 01:01:55,133
My father is sick too,

766
01:01:56,050 --> 01:01:58,094
but I can't even take care of him.

767
01:01:58,177 --> 01:01:59,095
Right.

768
01:02:00,138 --> 01:02:01,139
I heard.

769
01:02:02,390 --> 01:02:05,059
He was one strong man.

770
01:02:05,810 --> 01:02:09,313
He wouldn't budge
no matter how much I challenged him.

771
01:02:11,899 --> 01:02:13,901
So I kept at it.

772
01:02:15,695 --> 01:02:17,113
But I wouldn't have done it

773
01:02:18,239 --> 01:02:19,866
had I known this would happen.

774
01:02:20,908 --> 01:02:23,911
Do you know
what the last thing I said to him was?

775
01:02:25,455 --> 01:02:27,290
"I'll see you at your funeral."

776
01:02:33,629 --> 01:02:34,964
This darn mouth of mine.

777
01:02:35,548 --> 01:02:36,966
I should've been more careful.

778
01:02:41,387 --> 01:02:44,015
I've never challenged my mother before.

779
01:02:46,267 --> 01:02:47,935
Are you bragging right now?

780
01:02:48,019 --> 01:02:49,145
My mother left home

781
01:02:49,896 --> 01:02:51,773
when I was very little.

782
01:02:53,149 --> 01:02:55,693
My father was abusive and cheated on her.

783
01:02:58,404 --> 01:02:59,947
So I grew up without her.

784
01:03:01,741 --> 01:03:03,117
Then she got dementia,

785
01:03:04,327 --> 01:03:07,163
so I took her out of the nursing home
and have been living with her.

786
01:03:08,956 --> 01:03:11,667
It's my wish
to argue with her when she's sane.

787
01:03:11,751 --> 01:03:12,585
I…

788
01:03:12,668 --> 01:03:15,296
I had no idea.

789
01:03:15,379 --> 01:03:16,380
All of us

790
01:03:17,256 --> 01:03:19,842
have burdens that we must carry in life.

791
01:03:20,718 --> 01:03:23,012
Even those who look the most carefree

792
01:03:23,721 --> 01:03:25,973
carry heavy stones in their pockets.

793
01:03:27,683 --> 01:03:28,601
So…

794
01:03:29,227 --> 01:03:30,853
don't be jealous

795
01:03:31,479 --> 01:03:32,855
or blame yourself.

796
01:03:33,648 --> 01:03:35,817
I'm sure your father knows
how much you care.

797
01:05:08,117 --> 01:05:09,577
I tracked the truck.

798
01:05:09,660 --> 01:05:13,331
It left for your house in Hanil-dong
from the warehouse in Gyeonggi Province.

799
01:05:13,414 --> 01:05:14,290
What is this?

800
01:05:14,373 --> 01:05:16,042
So all that money is at home?

801
01:05:16,125 --> 01:05:17,960
That's impossible.

802
01:05:18,044 --> 01:05:20,546
Even if an apple crate
holds 600 million won,

803
01:05:20,630 --> 01:05:23,215
he'd need a total of 1,500 crates.

804
01:05:23,299 --> 01:05:27,219
He'd need more than just a storage room.
It'd require about 100 pyeongs of space.

805
01:05:27,303 --> 01:05:30,348
Could there be
a secret space in our house?

806
01:05:30,431 --> 01:05:31,682
Or a warehouse perhaps?

807
01:05:31,766 --> 01:05:34,560
We stopped by the district office
to check the floor plans,

808
01:05:34,644 --> 01:05:36,896
but we found nothing.

809
01:05:36,979 --> 01:05:37,855
Then what is this?

810
01:05:37,939 --> 01:05:39,315
Last night,

811
01:05:39,398 --> 01:05:42,068
Grandfather told me something when we met.

812
01:05:44,612 --> 01:05:45,488
What is it?

813
01:05:45,571 --> 01:05:47,073
Do you have something to say?

814
01:05:48,366 --> 01:05:51,869
Lady, come to my house
if a war breaks out.

815
01:05:51,953 --> 01:05:55,247
We have an air-raid shelter.

816
01:05:55,331 --> 01:05:57,041
You can hide there.

817
01:05:57,124 --> 01:05:58,960
He mentioned an air-raid shelter.

818
01:05:59,043 --> 01:05:59,919
An air-raid shelter?

819
01:06:00,002 --> 01:06:01,212
In our house?

820
01:06:01,295 --> 01:06:02,588
That can't be.

821
01:06:02,672 --> 01:06:03,965
He was probably rambling.

822
01:06:04,048 --> 01:06:05,675
We have something similar.

823
01:06:08,427 --> 01:06:10,304
He told me about how he had built

824
01:06:10,388 --> 01:06:12,264
a panic room.

825
01:06:12,348 --> 01:06:13,933
You're right. I heard too.

826
01:06:14,016 --> 01:06:15,226
But where is it?

827
01:06:15,309 --> 01:06:16,852
We only heard about it.

828
01:06:16,936 --> 01:06:19,230
None of us knows where it is.

829
01:06:19,313 --> 01:06:22,066
Even the floor plan didn't show anything.

830
01:06:22,149 --> 01:06:23,359
That's true,

831
01:06:23,442 --> 01:06:26,821
but there could be a secret floor plan.

832
01:06:29,240 --> 01:06:31,701
If the money was here like Grace said,

833
01:06:31,784 --> 01:06:32,952
then I would've known.

834
01:06:33,035 --> 01:06:36,038
All that money won't fit
in a couple safes.

835
01:06:37,498 --> 01:06:38,833
Yes, and we also have that room.

836
01:06:38,916 --> 01:06:41,002
You know the movie
with a secret room, Shock Room?

837
01:06:41,085 --> 01:06:42,920
It's Panic Room, you idiot.

838
01:06:44,630 --> 01:06:46,507
I heard this place had a panic room.

839
01:06:49,760 --> 01:06:51,345
Do you know about it?

840
01:06:55,933 --> 01:06:57,309
This isn't the Yongdu-ri Quintet.

841
01:06:57,393 --> 01:06:58,227
It's a trio.

842
01:06:58,310 --> 01:07:01,397
They'll join us for drinks later
after we finish patrolling.

843
01:07:03,566 --> 01:07:04,734
Who's that at this hour?

844
01:07:04,817 --> 01:07:06,652
Maybe they're those men
from earlier today.

845
01:07:06,736 --> 01:07:09,655
We should've brought a Taser or something.

846
01:07:10,489 --> 01:07:11,699
-It's a taxi.
-A taxi?

847
01:07:11,782 --> 01:07:13,284
They drove a black van.

848
01:07:16,495 --> 01:07:17,580
Who could they be?

849
01:07:18,164 --> 01:07:20,458
Why would they bring
a suitcase here at this hour?

850
01:07:21,083 --> 01:07:22,626
Isn't this what they say about killers

851
01:07:22,710 --> 01:07:24,336
-on the news?
-Should I call them?

852
01:07:24,420 --> 01:07:25,504
Should I?

853
01:08:04,627 --> 01:08:05,711
How have you been?

854
01:08:07,755 --> 01:08:08,923
I definitely…

855
01:08:10,424 --> 01:08:11,383
had…

856
01:08:12,676 --> 01:08:14,386
a good dream last night.

857
01:08:41,497 --> 01:08:42,414
I'm sorry.

858
01:08:42,498 --> 01:08:45,543
This is everything except for the money
spent on the flight and hotel.

859
01:08:45,626 --> 01:08:47,419
I bought an apartment in the U.S.

860
01:08:47,503 --> 01:08:48,921
but I'll get the money back.

861
01:08:49,004 --> 01:08:51,340
I'll give it to you once I get it.

862
01:08:51,423 --> 01:08:52,550
I'm truly sorry.

863
01:08:54,593 --> 01:08:55,594
Do you even know

864
01:08:55,678 --> 01:08:57,930
what you've done?

865
01:08:58,013 --> 01:09:00,182
Giving back that money won't cut it.

866
01:09:00,266 --> 01:09:01,767
-Mom.
-I'm aware of that.

867
01:09:01,851 --> 01:09:03,519
I know it's unforgivable.

868
01:09:05,229 --> 01:09:06,063
I'm truly…

869
01:09:07,398 --> 01:09:08,232
sorry.

870
01:09:08,941 --> 01:09:11,110
It's late, and we all need to sleep.

871
01:09:11,193 --> 01:09:12,278
Go to bed for now.

872
01:09:13,070 --> 01:09:14,363
Okay. You can sleep

873
01:09:14,446 --> 01:09:16,115
-over there--
-Don't be absurd.

874
01:09:17,449 --> 01:09:19,869
I don't want to see you
or that thing, so leave.

875
01:09:19,952 --> 01:09:22,621
His name is Geon-u.

876
01:09:23,998 --> 01:09:26,834
And you have no right
to tell them to leave.

877
01:09:26,917 --> 01:09:28,794
This isn't even our house.

878
01:09:30,504 --> 01:09:31,714
He's right, Seon-hwa.

879
01:09:34,884 --> 01:09:37,303
So you're going to live
with someone else's baby?

880
01:09:37,386 --> 01:09:38,762
He's my son!

881
01:09:38,846 --> 01:09:41,348
I cut his umbilical cord,
sang lullabies to him every night,

882
01:09:41,432 --> 01:09:42,474
and bathed him myself.

883
01:09:42,558 --> 01:09:44,101
Geon-u

884
01:09:44,643 --> 01:09:47,021
said "Dad" before he could even say "Mom"!

885
01:09:55,404 --> 01:09:56,405
Get up.

886
01:10:09,460 --> 01:10:10,753
But…

887
01:10:21,889 --> 01:10:23,891
We need to clear up some stuff.

888
01:10:27,102 --> 01:10:28,395
What should we call each other?

889
01:10:28,896 --> 01:10:31,065
You know my age,
so we can't be like how we used to be.

890
01:10:31,148 --> 01:10:32,566
I don't care.

891
01:10:32,650 --> 01:10:34,401
I care. I'm older than you.

892
01:10:34,485 --> 01:10:37,404
Do you want me to treat you like one?

893
01:10:38,614 --> 01:10:39,448
Ma'am?

894
01:10:41,533 --> 01:10:43,869
I didn't return
so we could live together again.

895
01:10:45,746 --> 01:10:47,665
-Then?
-I came to return everything.

896
01:10:48,749 --> 01:10:49,583
And Jun-ho--

897
01:10:52,419 --> 01:10:55,923
That bastard is planning
to use you as his scapegoat.

898
01:10:56,882 --> 01:10:58,676
Stop him, or you'll end up in prison.

899
01:10:58,759 --> 01:11:00,552
So you came here just to tell me that?

900
01:11:03,973 --> 01:11:05,015
I was worried.

901
01:11:06,100 --> 01:11:08,978
I only got married to mooch off

902
01:11:10,145 --> 01:11:12,189
of a stupid, wealthy guy.

903
01:11:17,653 --> 01:11:19,530
So I didn't expect you…

904
01:11:21,740 --> 01:11:22,825
to care

905
01:11:24,326 --> 01:11:25,452
so much about me.

906
01:11:30,332 --> 01:11:32,376
No one has ever

907
01:11:32,459 --> 01:11:34,670
treated me the way you did.

908
01:11:34,753 --> 01:11:37,089
I couldn't forget how well…

909
01:11:39,842 --> 01:11:41,093
you treated me.

910
01:11:42,469 --> 01:11:44,888
I couldn't even eat well.

911
01:11:47,558 --> 01:11:48,976
That's why I'm here.

912
01:11:49,059 --> 01:11:50,519
So you came here to tell me that?

913
01:11:50,602 --> 01:11:52,521
Really? And once you're done,

914
01:11:52,896 --> 01:11:54,106
will you leave again?

915
01:11:58,360 --> 01:11:59,737
I feel shame too.

916
01:12:01,155 --> 01:12:02,156
I can't live with you.

917
01:12:02,239 --> 01:12:03,073
No.

918
01:12:03,699 --> 01:12:05,117
I must live with you.

919
01:12:08,162 --> 01:12:09,621
I don't care why you're here.

920
01:12:09,705 --> 01:12:11,540
I'm going to live with you.

921
01:12:13,334 --> 01:12:15,169
I'll never let you or my son leave again.

922
01:12:18,505 --> 01:12:19,590
Go if you want.

923
01:12:20,257 --> 01:12:22,051
I'll find you no matter where you are.

924
01:12:22,134 --> 01:12:22,968
You really

925
01:12:23,969 --> 01:12:25,721
don't listen, do you?

926
01:12:27,723 --> 01:12:29,516
-I'm older than you.
-Be quiet.

927
01:12:41,445 --> 01:12:42,446
-So--
-Excuse me.

928
01:12:42,529 --> 01:12:45,449
Have some of this.

929
01:12:45,532 --> 01:12:46,658
Thank you.

930
01:12:46,742 --> 01:12:47,743
Thank you.

931
01:12:48,827 --> 01:12:50,621
She's my master's…

932
01:12:50,704 --> 01:12:53,207
-She doesn't look like a mom.
-Stop staring.

933
01:12:53,290 --> 01:12:55,417
I heard she made quite an entrance.

934
01:12:55,501 --> 01:12:56,335
It was insane.

935
01:12:56,418 --> 01:12:58,420
My husband told me about it.

936
01:12:58,504 --> 01:13:01,924
She appeared in the middle of the night
while holding Buddha's head.

937
01:13:02,007 --> 01:13:04,259
My husband was so shocked.

938
01:13:04,343 --> 01:13:07,554
He keeps getting sleep paralysis

939
01:13:07,638 --> 01:13:08,639
and waking up.

940
01:13:08,722 --> 01:13:09,723
I told you.

941
01:13:09,807 --> 01:13:12,309
Chun-sik needs some black goat extract.

942
01:13:12,393 --> 01:13:13,268
Then feed him.

943
01:13:13,352 --> 01:13:14,228
Really?

944
01:13:14,311 --> 01:13:17,523
Is that golden Buddha really made of gold?

945
01:13:17,606 --> 01:13:18,607
Pure gold?

946
01:13:18,690 --> 01:13:19,942
Beats me.

947
01:13:23,529 --> 01:13:27,032
What does your hunch say? We should decide
between "like" or "dislike."

948
01:13:27,116 --> 01:13:28,409
-What do you mean?
-I mean…

949
01:13:28,492 --> 01:13:31,829
We'll run into her often,
so we need to know

950
01:13:31,912 --> 01:13:34,873
what kind of stance to take.

951
01:13:34,957 --> 01:13:36,583
Will we welcome or ignore her?

952
01:13:36,667 --> 01:13:37,668
Exactly.

953
01:13:37,751 --> 01:13:39,211
Is it like or dislike?

954
01:13:39,294 --> 01:13:40,879
We'll do as you say.

955
01:13:42,923 --> 01:13:44,425
I'm not sure yet.

956
01:13:46,927 --> 01:13:47,886
You're not?

957
01:13:48,387 --> 01:13:50,264
I feel bad for her,

958
01:13:50,931 --> 01:13:52,808
but something feels off too.

959
01:13:52,891 --> 01:13:54,601
I need to watch her a bit longer.

960
01:14:28,635 --> 01:14:29,636
He still remembered

961
01:14:30,262 --> 01:14:32,055
my size.

962
01:14:34,808 --> 01:14:37,519
A round brilliant cut?

963
01:14:45,736 --> 01:14:47,154
Didn't you go to work?

964
01:14:49,615 --> 01:14:50,449
Yes.

965
01:14:51,950 --> 01:14:53,494
But I forgot something.

966
01:15:03,837 --> 01:15:05,172
I'm going to return it.

967
01:15:06,215 --> 01:15:08,467
-I see.
-I thought about what you said.

968
01:15:09,051 --> 01:15:11,094
I think I pushed ahead too much.

969
01:15:12,471 --> 01:15:14,890
I'll return it on my way to work today.

970
01:15:16,183 --> 01:15:17,017
I see.

971
01:15:18,477 --> 01:15:19,645
Today?

972
01:15:20,312 --> 01:15:22,439
This isn't what's important right now.

973
01:15:23,440 --> 01:15:24,274
Don't feel bad.

974
01:15:24,358 --> 01:15:26,235
I'm really okay.

975
01:15:28,362 --> 01:15:29,196
I see.

976
01:15:30,656 --> 01:15:31,573
Okay then.

977
01:15:48,757 --> 01:15:49,925
What?

978
01:15:51,051 --> 01:15:52,052
What is it?

979
01:15:52,678 --> 01:15:53,679
I just

980
01:15:53,929 --> 01:15:55,305
tried it on.

981
01:15:55,389 --> 01:15:57,599
It was a new design.
I wanted to study the trends.

982
01:15:57,683 --> 01:16:00,936
I can't slack off
just because I'm taking a break.

983
01:16:03,564 --> 01:16:06,233
That's true.

984
01:16:06,316 --> 01:16:07,859
I liked the ring.

985
01:16:07,943 --> 01:16:10,654
You know that rings suit me awfully well.

986
01:16:11,530 --> 01:16:12,614
You have a good eye.

987
01:16:12,698 --> 01:16:13,865
I'll give you that.

988
01:16:13,949 --> 01:16:15,284
But…

989
01:16:15,367 --> 01:16:17,703
it's just that.

990
01:16:17,786 --> 01:16:20,163
So don't misinterpret my actions.

991
01:16:21,290 --> 01:16:22,291
Wait.

992
01:16:23,250 --> 01:16:26,003
Are you sure
you've finished analyzing the trends?

993
01:16:26,628 --> 01:16:27,879
Maybe study it more.

994
01:16:29,256 --> 01:16:30,632
I'm done analyzing it.

995
01:16:30,716 --> 01:16:31,800
I'll get going then.

996
01:16:41,184 --> 01:16:42,102
Hae-in.

997
01:16:42,728 --> 01:16:43,895
I won't return it.

998
01:16:43,979 --> 01:16:46,815
I'll leave it where it was before.

999
01:16:46,898 --> 01:16:48,609
You need to analyze the trends,

1000
01:16:48,692 --> 01:16:50,402
so wear it whenever you want.

1001
01:16:57,618 --> 01:16:59,494
A panic room? Like the one in the movies?

1002
01:16:59,578 --> 01:17:02,039
For when there's a nuclear bomb?
Where there are guns

1003
01:17:02,122 --> 01:17:03,540
and years' worth of food?

1004
01:17:04,124 --> 01:17:07,628
I'm not sure about that part,
but the chairman did mention a panic room.

1005
01:17:07,711 --> 01:17:09,755
But no one knows where it's located.

1006
01:17:09,838 --> 01:17:11,173
I see.

1007
01:17:11,256 --> 01:17:13,467
-What about on the register?
-It wasn't in there.

1008
01:17:13,550 --> 01:17:14,426
Ask the designer.

1009
01:17:14,509 --> 01:17:15,344
He passed away.

1010
01:17:15,427 --> 01:17:17,846
The son took over the firm.

1011
01:17:17,929 --> 01:17:19,306
Then ask him.

1012
01:17:19,389 --> 01:17:20,724
I did,

1013
01:17:20,807 --> 01:17:21,725
and he doesn't know.

1014
01:17:21,808 --> 01:17:24,353
I asked for the floor plan,
but he had none.

1015
01:17:24,436 --> 01:17:27,022
I kept calling him
and now he won't pick up anymore.

1016
01:17:27,105 --> 01:17:27,939
Really?

1017
01:17:28,523 --> 01:17:29,650
What'll you do then?

1018
01:17:29,733 --> 01:17:31,526
There's not much I can do.

1019
01:17:31,610 --> 01:17:33,862
Someone else needs to convince him.

1020
01:17:34,529 --> 01:17:35,989
Who?

1021
01:17:36,073 --> 01:17:37,032
-You.
-Me?

1022
01:17:37,115 --> 01:17:39,618
Goodness, we meet again.

1023
01:17:39,701 --> 01:17:41,578
You never know the future.

1024
01:17:41,662 --> 01:17:42,746
I totally agree.

1025
01:17:42,829 --> 01:17:44,790
I've met my lifesaver again.

1026
01:17:45,415 --> 01:17:47,376
Gosh, I don't deserve that title.

1027
01:17:50,087 --> 01:17:51,338
How's the building in Pangyo?

1028
01:17:51,421 --> 01:17:53,173
Good, and it's all thanks to you.

1029
01:17:53,256 --> 01:17:54,508
I almost lost it.

1030
01:17:55,217 --> 01:17:58,970
By the way,
I heard my friend here pestered you.

1031
01:17:59,054 --> 01:17:59,888
I apologize.

1032
01:17:59,971 --> 01:18:03,100
I didn't want to get involved
in something complicated.

1033
01:18:03,892 --> 01:18:06,144
No, I'm sorry about asking such a favor.

1034
01:18:06,770 --> 01:18:08,730
If this panic room
was made for evacuation,

1035
01:18:08,814 --> 01:18:12,150
air pipes and electrical installations
for ventilation and communication

1036
01:18:12,234 --> 01:18:13,819
should have been installed.

1037
01:18:13,902 --> 01:18:15,654
But I couldn't find any on the floor plan.

1038
01:18:15,737 --> 01:18:18,198
How will we find it?
We'd have to turn the house upside down.

1039
01:18:18,281 --> 01:18:19,116
What's interesting

1040
01:18:19,199 --> 01:18:21,743
is that his elevator
that connects to the basement

1041
01:18:21,827 --> 01:18:24,705
was specially built unlike the others.

1042
01:18:25,288 --> 01:18:26,581
His elevator?

1043
01:18:26,665 --> 01:18:28,458
It never felt different to me.

1044
01:18:37,092 --> 01:18:38,927
It has two doors.

1045
01:18:39,010 --> 01:18:41,763
The back side is a door as well.

1046
01:18:41,847 --> 01:18:44,433
The front door leads to the family room,

1047
01:18:44,516 --> 01:18:48,228
but the back door leads
to a whole different space. Is that it?

1048
01:18:48,311 --> 01:18:49,646
And that's the panic room?

1049
01:18:49,730 --> 01:18:52,441
That's my guess, but I'd have to check.

1050
01:18:52,524 --> 01:18:56,069
-Can't we just raid the place?
-There's tight security.

1051
01:18:56,153 --> 01:18:57,904
We'll be sued for trespassing.

1052
01:18:57,988 --> 01:19:01,366
But what if Seul-hee
finds it before we do?

1053
01:19:01,450 --> 01:19:03,118
I spoke with his doctor today.

1054
01:19:03,201 --> 01:19:05,287
His doctor told me
that he hasn't been receiving

1055
01:19:05,370 --> 01:19:07,247
any mandatory treatments

1056
01:19:07,330 --> 01:19:09,040
like rehabilitation or memory training

1057
01:19:09,124 --> 01:19:10,876
ever since he woke up and returned home.

1058
01:19:10,959 --> 01:19:14,254
He's likely out of medication,
but he hasn't made another appointment.

1059
01:19:14,337 --> 01:19:16,631
What? I knew this would happen.

1060
01:19:16,715 --> 01:19:18,258
What should we do?

1061
01:19:18,842 --> 01:19:21,303
We can report them for confinement

1062
01:19:21,386 --> 01:19:23,221
and enter the house

1063
01:19:23,305 --> 01:19:24,264
with the police.

1064
01:19:25,223 --> 01:19:26,850
And check out the elevator?

1065
01:19:27,517 --> 01:19:30,437
Let's all go first thing in the morning.

1066
01:20:10,644 --> 01:20:11,978
You're back.

1067
01:20:14,898 --> 01:20:15,899
I knew it.

1068
01:20:16,525 --> 01:20:17,901
You seemed a bit off

1069
01:20:18,652 --> 01:20:21,571
ever since Hae-in came by.

1070
01:20:24,199 --> 01:20:26,493
Do you come to your senses
every now and then?

1071
01:20:26,576 --> 01:20:29,579
But the duration is too short
for you to do anything.

1072
01:20:29,663 --> 01:20:31,414
You can't request help.

1073
01:20:31,498 --> 01:20:32,666
You can't move freely.

1074
01:20:32,749 --> 01:20:34,125
You have no phone either.

1075
01:20:34,209 --> 01:20:36,253
This place must be hell, mustn't it?

1076
01:20:37,254 --> 01:20:38,129
You're right.

1077
01:20:38,713 --> 01:20:39,589
This is

1078
01:20:40,715 --> 01:20:41,675
a living hell.

1079
01:20:41,758 --> 01:20:42,759
And…

1080
01:20:43,760 --> 01:20:44,970
I'm being punished.

1081
01:20:45,053 --> 01:20:46,888
That's why I gave you that pill.

1082
01:20:46,972 --> 01:20:49,808
So that you could sleep in peace
with no worries.

1083
01:20:49,891 --> 01:20:51,560
So why aren't you taking them?

1084
01:20:51,643 --> 01:20:53,436
Moh Seul-hee.

1085
01:20:53,520 --> 01:20:56,648
Was this always your motive
for coming here?

1086
01:21:01,194 --> 01:21:03,530
Then did you think I truly loved you

1087
01:21:03,613 --> 01:21:05,031
or something?

1088
01:21:07,993 --> 01:21:09,411
Aren't I just terrible?

1089
01:21:09,494 --> 01:21:10,745
Don't you miss your kids?

1090
01:21:10,829 --> 01:21:11,872
You can go.

1091
01:21:11,955 --> 01:21:13,164
Just tell me

1092
01:21:14,082 --> 01:21:15,959
where your secret fund is.

1093
01:21:18,545 --> 01:21:21,381
There's nothing you can do
when you're only sane

1094
01:21:21,464 --> 01:21:23,341
for a short moment at a time.

1095
01:21:23,425 --> 01:21:24,843
Just tell me,

1096
01:21:24,926 --> 01:21:27,304
and everything will be fine.

1097
01:21:31,182 --> 01:21:32,017
Tell me!

1098
01:22:48,593 --> 01:22:49,886
What's going on?

1099
01:22:50,512 --> 01:22:51,346
Hyun-woo.

1100
01:22:51,429 --> 01:22:53,640
Did you call an ambulance as well?

1101
01:22:53,723 --> 01:22:55,892
No, the officer I contacted
hasn't arrived yet.

1102
01:22:55,976 --> 01:22:56,977
Then what's going on?

1103
01:22:57,060 --> 01:22:58,395
Did something happen?

1104
01:23:03,400 --> 01:23:04,734
What is it?

1105
01:23:05,527 --> 01:23:06,528
What's going on?

1106
01:23:09,739 --> 01:23:10,949
Tell me.

1107
01:23:14,160 --> 01:23:15,704
-Move.
-You can't enter.

1108
01:23:15,787 --> 01:23:16,621
Jeez.

1109
01:23:16,705 --> 01:23:18,415
Hong Man-dae, age 80, has dementia.

1110
01:23:18,498 --> 01:23:21,084
We believe a cervical spine fracture
was the cause of death.

1111
01:23:21,167 --> 01:23:23,837
He'll be taken to Daemang Hospital soon.

1112
01:23:25,046 --> 01:23:26,756
Dad!

1113
01:23:31,011 --> 01:23:33,930
Dad!

1114
01:23:50,864 --> 01:23:51,698
Dad?

1115
01:23:52,532 --> 01:23:53,366
Father.

1116
01:23:54,492 --> 01:23:55,702
Father.

1117
01:23:55,785 --> 01:23:57,579
We're here.

1118
01:23:57,662 --> 01:23:58,663
We're here now.

1119
01:24:00,498 --> 01:24:01,332
Dad…

1120
01:24:02,167 --> 01:24:03,668
Do something…

1121
01:24:05,420 --> 01:24:06,254
Beom-jun.

1122
01:24:07,422 --> 01:24:09,257
Do something.

1123
01:24:09,340 --> 01:24:12,135
His hands are still warm.

1124
01:24:12,886 --> 01:24:13,887
No.

1125
01:24:13,970 --> 01:24:15,305
What's going on?

1126
01:24:15,388 --> 01:24:16,222
Honey.

1127
01:24:16,765 --> 01:24:18,016
Sir.

1128
01:24:18,600 --> 01:24:21,269
Please give him CPR or something.

1129
01:24:21,352 --> 01:24:22,896
-Dad…
-I'm sorry.

1130
01:24:22,979 --> 01:24:24,898
Do something, please.

1131
01:24:24,981 --> 01:24:26,649
I'm sorry. We need to move him.

1132
01:24:27,692 --> 01:24:29,778
We need to move him. I'm sorry.

1133
01:24:29,861 --> 01:24:31,821
-Dad!
-Excuse us.

1134
01:24:32,739 --> 01:24:33,823
Dad!

1135
01:24:34,365 --> 01:24:35,617
Wait!

1136
01:24:35,700 --> 01:24:37,077
-Dad!
-I'm sorry.

1137
01:24:37,160 --> 01:24:39,621
-Wait.
-We need to move him. I'm sorry.

1138
01:24:39,704 --> 01:24:41,456
-We have to move. I'm sorry.
-Dad!

1139
01:24:41,539 --> 01:24:42,791
-I'm sorry.
-Dad!

1140
01:24:42,874 --> 01:24:43,917
Grandfather.

1141
01:24:44,501 --> 01:24:45,418
Grandfather.

1142
01:24:48,755 --> 01:24:49,672
Dad…

1143
01:24:51,091 --> 01:24:52,842
Dad…

1144
01:24:54,052 --> 01:24:55,261
Dad…

1145
01:25:05,355 --> 01:25:08,233
A prominent business mogul
passed away early this morning.

1146
01:25:08,733 --> 01:25:11,361
After beginning
as a shoeshine boy in the streets

1147
01:25:11,444 --> 01:25:13,696
and building Queens Group
into an industry leader,

1148
01:25:13,780 --> 01:25:16,116
Hong Man-dae,
the former Queens Group chairman,

1149
01:25:16,199 --> 01:25:19,035
has died at the age of 80.

1150
01:25:20,036 --> 01:25:24,749
He suffered a sudden heart attack
a month ago and had been in a coma.

1151
01:25:24,833 --> 01:25:29,129
Despite recently waking up,
he had showed signs of vascular dementia.

1152
01:25:30,296 --> 01:25:34,926
The industry is closely monitoring
Queens Group's leadership situation.

1153
01:25:35,009 --> 01:25:38,888
Hong signed the power of attorney
to his domestic partner, Moh Seul-hee,

1154
01:25:38,972 --> 01:25:42,016
which grants her rights,
such as control of his shares and house.

1155
01:25:42,934 --> 01:25:45,186
However, due to his passing,

1156
01:25:45,270 --> 01:25:47,730
her rights will become null and void.

1157
01:27:15,401 --> 01:27:16,903
Due to Chairman Hong's death,

1158
01:27:16,986 --> 01:27:19,739
his entire fortune will be handed out

1159
01:27:19,822 --> 01:27:21,366
according to his notarized will.

1160
01:27:21,449 --> 01:27:25,411
This takes effect immediately
without needing the court's approval.

1161
01:27:26,788 --> 01:27:28,748
Did you get that?

1162
01:27:28,831 --> 01:27:30,083
Pack up and get going.

1163
01:27:30,166 --> 01:27:31,209
Shouldn't we focus

1164
01:27:32,126 --> 01:27:34,212
on wishing him peace for now?

1165
01:27:35,255 --> 01:27:38,341
We can discuss such matters later.

1166
01:27:41,469 --> 01:27:43,221
He loved this house.

1167
01:27:45,640 --> 01:27:46,724
Please give him

1168
01:27:48,226 --> 01:27:49,519
one final tour.

1169
01:27:51,062 --> 01:27:52,188
You little…

1170
01:29:06,387 --> 01:29:07,430
You're blessed

1171
01:29:07,513 --> 01:29:09,515
with a handsome and smart son.

1172
01:29:09,599 --> 01:29:10,433
Yes.

1173
01:29:10,516 --> 01:29:11,976
He's good at boxing

1174
01:29:12,060 --> 01:29:13,686
and swimming too.

1175
01:29:13,770 --> 01:29:15,063
Right.

1176
01:29:15,146 --> 01:29:15,980
Look here.

1177
01:29:16,064 --> 01:29:18,399
He even went to
a children's Marine Corps Camp.

1178
01:29:19,025 --> 01:29:20,610
He once

1179
01:29:20,693 --> 01:29:22,737
even saved a kid from drowning.

1180
01:29:25,948 --> 01:29:28,117
-What's going on?
-Don't go there.

1181
01:29:28,201 --> 01:29:31,704
-What's going on?
-Hurry up!

1182
01:29:31,788 --> 01:29:35,416
-What's going on?
-What's happening?

1183
01:29:40,421 --> 01:29:42,131
Hae-in!

1184
01:29:42,757 --> 01:29:44,217
Hae-in!

1185
01:30:31,973 --> 01:30:32,974
-Two.
-Two.

1186
01:30:35,476 --> 01:30:36,352
-Three.
-Three.

1187
01:30:40,314 --> 01:30:41,816
Why did you go in there?

1188
01:30:42,692 --> 01:30:44,110
Are you okay? Come along.

1189
01:30:56,497 --> 01:30:58,332
Su-wan…

1190
01:30:59,333 --> 01:31:01,794
No, Su-wan…

1191
01:31:02,962 --> 01:31:04,797
Su-wan, please!

1192
01:31:06,841 --> 01:31:08,176
My poor son!

1193
01:31:10,261 --> 01:31:11,554
Su-wan!

1194
01:31:11,637 --> 01:31:14,432
QUEEN OF TEARS

1195
01:31:44,795 --> 01:31:47,507
Hae-in. Thank you.

1196
01:31:47,590 --> 01:31:48,674
It was you, wasn't it?

1197
01:31:48,758 --> 01:31:50,801
I told you. I want her to live.

1198
01:31:51,677 --> 01:31:53,846
I'm going to leave once I'm done here.

1199
01:31:53,930 --> 01:31:55,306
Balsam?

1200
01:31:55,389 --> 01:31:57,892
It signifies my excitement
and hope for the first snow

1201
01:31:57,975 --> 01:31:59,352
that I thought I'd never see.

1202
01:31:59,435 --> 01:32:00,853
This is…

1203
01:32:01,354 --> 01:32:03,731
what you call true fate.

1204
01:32:03,814 --> 01:32:06,192
You're going to ruin this all
just for Hong Hae-in?

1205
01:32:06,275 --> 01:32:07,652
He took the bait.

1206
01:32:08,110 --> 01:32:10,863
Keep Eun-sung in the loop
so that he'll feel anxious…

1207
01:32:12,114 --> 01:32:13,366
Hae-in!

1208
01:32:13,449 --> 01:32:15,618
There's something
I didn't tell you as well.

1209
01:32:20,498 --> 01:32:22,500
Subtitle translation by Soo-ji Kim
